{"name": "timberborn", "game": "Timberborn", "version": "0.0.5", "hidden": false, "groups": [{"name": "Game Options", "options": [{"name": "progression_balancing", "display_name": "Progression Balancing", "description": "A system that can move progression earlier, to try and prevent the player from getting stuck and bored early.\n\nA lower setting means more getting stuck. A higher setting means less getting stuck.", "randomizable": true, "visibility": 15, "type": "NamedRange", "default": 50, "min": 0, "max": 99, "presets": {"disabled": 0, "normal": 50, "extreme": 99}}, {"name": "accessibility", "display_name": "Accessibility", "description": "Set rules for reachability of your items/locations.\n\n**Full:** ensure everything can be reached and acquired.\n\n**Minimal:** ensure what is needed to reach your goal can be acquired.", "randomizable": true, "visibility": 15, "type": "Choice", "default": 0, "choices": [{"name": "full", "display_name": "Full", "value": 0}, {"name": "minimal", "display_name": "Minimal", "value": 2}]}, {"name": "faction", "display_name": "Faction", "description": "Which beaver faction to play as?\n- folktails: Nature-loving beavers with unique buildings like Beehive, Aquatic Farmhouse, Bakery.\n- iron_teeth: Industrial beavers with unique buildings like Steam Engine, Rowhouse, Coffee Brewery.\n\nUse ``random`` in YAML for a random faction per seed.\nThe client will block connection if you load the wrong faction in-game.\n\nNOTE: Iron Teeth must be unlocked in-game before selecting it here.\nUnlock it by reaching average well-being 8 in a Folktails game first,\nor the Archipelago mod may auto-unlock it for you.", "randomizable": true, "visibility": 15, "type": "Choice", "default": 0, "choices": [{"name": "folktails", "display_name": "Folktails", "value": 0}, {"name": "iron_teeth", "display_name": "Iron Teeth", "value": 1}]}, {"name": "goal_selection", "display_name": "Goal Selection", "description": "Which victory conditions are in play? Pick any combination, or use\n``random-range-1-3`` in YAML to randomize how many are active.\n\nPossible values:\n- **Wonder**: Build your faction's Wonder building.\n- **Population**: Reach the target beaver population (see population_goal).\n- **Droughts**: Survive a number of drought cycles (see drought_cycles_goal).\n- **Badtides**: Survive a number of badtide cycles (see badtide_cycles_goal).\n- **Well-being**: Reach a target average well-being level (see wellbeing_goal).\n- **Bots**: Construct a number of bots (see bots_goal).\n- **Water Storage**: Reach a water storage capacity threshold (see water_storage_goal).\n\nAt least one goal must be selected. If the resolved set is empty,\nthe game falls back to Wonder.", "randomizable": false, "visibility": 15, "type": "OptionSet", "default": ["Wonder"], "options": ["Badtides", "Bots", "Droughts", "Population", "Water Storage", "Well-being", "Wonder"]}, {"name": "goal_requirement", "display_name": "Goal Requirement", "description": "Of the goals selected in *Goal Selection*, how many must be completed?\n- any: Complete ANY ONE of the selected goals to win.\n- all: Complete ALL selected goals to win.", "randomizable": true, "visibility": 15, "type": "Choice", "default": 0, "choices": [{"name": "any", "display_name": "Any", "value": 0}, {"name": "all", "display_name": "All", "value": 1}]}, {"name": "randomization_style", "display_name": "Randomization Style", "description": "Which buildings are shuffled into the multiworld?\n- shuffle: Only buildings that normally cost Science Points are randomized.\n- grand_chaos: All buildings (including basic ones like Paths and Stockpiles) are randomized.", "randomizable": true, "visibility": 15, "type": "Choice", "default": 0, "choices": [{"name": "shuffle", "display_name": "Shuffle", "value": 0}, {"name": "grand_chaos", "display_name": "Grand Chaos", "value": 1}]}, {"name": "population_goal", "display_name": "Population Goal", "description": "When 'Population' goal is active, the total count required (see population_mode).", "randomizable": true, "visibility": 15, "type": "Range", "default": 100, "min": 10, "max": 500}, {"name": "population_mode", "display_name": "Population Mode", "description": "When the 'Population' goal is active, what counts toward the target?\n- beavers_only: Only beavers count.\n- bots_only: Only bots count.\n- beavers_and_bots: Both beavers and bots count together.", "randomizable": true, "visibility": 15, "type": "Choice", "default": 0, "choices": [{"name": "beavers_only", "display_name": "Beavers Only", "value": 0}, {"name": "bots_only", "display_name": "Bots Only", "value": 1}, {"name": "beavers_and_bots", "display_name": "Beavers And Bots", "value": 2}]}, {"name": "drought_cycles_goal", "display_name": "Drought Cycles Goal", "description": "When 'Droughts' goal is active, the number of drought cycles to survive.", "randomizable": true, "visibility": 15, "type": "Range", "default": 25, "min": 5, "max": 100}, {"name": "badtide_cycles_goal", "display_name": "Badtide Cycles Goal", "description": "When 'Badtides' goal is active, the number of badtide cycles to survive.", "randomizable": true, "visibility": 15, "type": "Range", "default": 10, "min": 1, "max": 50}, {"name": "wellbeing_goal", "display_name": "Well-being Goal", "description": "When 'Well-being' goal is active, the average well-being level to reach.", "randomizable": true, "visibility": 15, "type": "Range", "default": 15, "min": 5, "max": 20}, {"name": "bots_goal", "display_name": "Bots Goal", "description": "When 'Bots' goal is active, the number of bots to construct.", "randomizable": true, "visibility": 15, "type": "Range", "default": 10, "min": 1, "max": 50}, {"name": "water_storage_goal", "display_name": "Water Storage Goal", "description": "When 'Water Storage' goal is active, the water storage capacity to reach.", "randomizable": true, "visibility": 15, "type": "Range", "default": 5000, "min": 500, "max": 50000}, {"name": "drought_difficulty", "display_name": "Drought Difficulty", "description": "Scaling factor (1\u20135) for how hard droughts are during the randomizer run.\nHigher values mean longer, more severe droughts.", "randomizable": true, "visibility": 15, "type": "Range", "default": 3, "min": 1, "max": 5}, {"name": "include_traps", "display_name": "Include Traps", "description": "If enabled, trap items (Hazardous Weather, Hungry Beavers, Thirsty Beavers) can appear in the item pool.", "randomizable": true, "visibility": 15, "type": "Toggle", "default": true}, {"name": "trap_mode", "display_name": "Trap Mode", "description": "How Hazardous Weather traps behave when a hazardous cycle is already active or pending:\n- queue: Weather traps wait until the current weather ends, then trigger in order.\n- skip: Weather traps are discarded if weather is already active.", "randomizable": true, "visibility": 15, "type": "Choice", "default": 0, "choices": [{"name": "queue", "display_name": "Queue", "value": 0}, {"name": "skip", "display_name": "Skip", "value": 1}]}, {"name": "max_science_cost", "display_name": "Max Science Cost", "description": "Maximum science cost for the most expensive shop location.", "randomizable": true, "visibility": 15, "type": "Range", "default": 5000, "min": 1000, "max": 20000}, {"name": "science_cost_multiplier", "display_name": "Science Cost Multiplier", "description": "Percentage multiplier applied to all shop science costs.\n50 = half price (faster unlocks), 100 = default, 200 = double price (slower).", "randomizable": true, "visibility": 15, "type": "Range", "default": 100, "min": 10, "max": 1000}, {"name": "skip_count", "display_name": "Skip Count", "description": "Number of Skip items added to the item pool. Skips let you check a shop location for free.", "randomizable": true, "visibility": 15, "type": "Range", "default": 3, "min": 0, "max": 10}, {"name": "progressive_items", "display_name": "Progressive Items", "description": "Merge related size-upgrade buildings into progressive item chains.\nEach receipt of a progressive item unlocks the next tier in the sequence\n(e.g. Progressive Platforms: Platform \u2192 Double Platform \u2192 Triple Platform).\n- off: Each building is a separate item (classic behavior).\n- grouped_random: Each chain is randomly enabled or disabled per seed.\n- on: All progressive chains are active.", "randomizable": true, "visibility": 15, "type": "Choice", "default": 2, "choices": [{"name": "off", "display_name": "Off", "value": 0}, {"name": "grouped_random", "display_name": "Grouped Random", "value": 1}, {"name": "on", "display_name": "On", "value": 2}]}, {"name": "include_population_milestones", "display_name": "Include Population Milestones", "description": "Include population milestone locations (beaver count thresholds, first born/grown).", "randomizable": true, "visibility": 15, "type": "Toggle", "default": true}, {"name": "include_wellbeing_milestones", "display_name": "Include Well-being Milestones", "description": "Include well-being milestone locations (well-being level thresholds).", "randomizable": true, "visibility": 15, "type": "Toggle", "default": true}, {"name": "include_survival_milestones", "display_name": "Include Survival Milestones", "description": "Include drought and badtide survival milestone locations.", "randomizable": true, "visibility": 15, "type": "Toggle", "default": true}, {"name": "include_wonder_milestone", "display_name": "Include Wonder Milestone", "description": "Include the Wonder completion milestone location.", "randomizable": true, "visibility": 15, "type": "Toggle", "default": true}, {"name": "force_early_items", "display_name": "Force Early Items", "description": "When enabled, essential early-game blueprints (Forester, Stairs, Levee, Gear Workshop)\nare forced into the first reachable sphere, guaranteeing they are available right away.\nPlatform and Floodgate are progression items and will also appear early, but are not\nforced into sphere 1 to avoid fill errors when milestones are disabled.\n\nWhen disabled, these items are placed freely like any other progression item and may\nappear anywhere in the multiworld. This makes the early game significantly harder and\nless predictable, but allows for more varied and challenging seeds.", "randomizable": true, "visibility": 15, "type": "Toggle", "default": true}, {"name": "extra_early_survival", "display_name": "Extra Early Survival", "description": "When enabled (alongside Force Early Items), one random survival building per category\n\u2014 housing, food, wellbeing \u2014 is forced into sphere 1 on top of the core essentials.\nEach seed picks different candidates so runs stay varied. Requires milestones enabled\nto avoid fill errors.\n\nDesigned to fix the \"useful item scatter\" problem where basic housing/food/wellbeing\nbuildings can otherwise arrive very late in the multiworld. Disable for lean seeds\nthat only force the core 4 progression items.", "randomizable": true, "visibility": 15, "type": "Toggle", "default": true}, {"name": "logic_difficulty", "display_name": "Logic Difficulty", "description": "Controls how strict the logic is for milestone accessibility.\n- standard: Milestones are gated by tier only (lenient \u2014 assumes creative survival).\n- strict: Survival milestones also require specific buildings\n  (e.g., badtide milestones require Levee + Floodgate, drought milestones require\n  water infrastructure). Ensures the solver places survival-critical items before\n  survival milestones become reachable.", "randomizable": true, "visibility": 15, "type": "Choice", "default": 1, "choices": [{"name": "standard", "display_name": "Standard", "value": 0}, {"name": "strict", "display_name": "Strict", "value": 1}]}], "collapsed": false}, {"name": "Item & Location Options", "options": [{"name": "local_items", "display_name": "Local Items", "description": "Forces these items to be in their native world.", "randomizable": false, "visibility": 15, "type": "OptionSet", "default": [], "opti